{{define "llm-correction-common-rules"}}
- preserve meaning
- preserve original language
- if the utterance mixes languages, keep each span in the language originally spoken;
  do not translate English words into Chinese, Japanese into English, etc.
- fix punctuation, spacing, capitalization, obvious ASR artifacts
- drop filler / discourse particles if meaning is unchanged
- dedupe accidental repeated words / phrases
- number words -> Arabic numerals when appropriate
{{end}}

{{define "llm-correction-common-examples"}}
- "um well I think I think we need three people" -> "I think we need 3 people"
- "嗯那个我们需要三个人，三个人去开会" -> "我们需要3个人去开会"
- "啊，我，那个，住在二十一楼" -> "我住在21楼"
- "用 grep 查一下 error log" -> "用 grep 查一下 error log"
{{end}}
